{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require bold environment warnings on wasteful food and drink packaging.",
        "additional_details": "Searching for tiny recycling logos or faint \"not currently recycled\" excuses, particularly for those with poor eyesight, is a pain! The red triangle will make waste instantly obvious, helping us to (a) bin it correctly, not contaminating other well-sorted material (b) avoid buying it, and (c) push suppliers away from it.\r\nWhile much packaging today is proudly waste-free, it should become the norm, we should be able to assume it is waste-free unless loud and clear warnings state otherwise.",
        "background": "All wasteful food and drink packaging should be labelled in a bold red warning triangle \"Not Waste-Free\".\r\n\r\nBy wasteful we mean not recyclable nor compostable. The label should be on the front panel.\r\n\r\nWaste-free living is what we want, is an Earthshot goal, and should be easy!",
